SIMPLE: rocker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rocker
<hw>Rock"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who rocks;
specifically, one who rocks a cradle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was I, sir, said the <qex>rocker</qex>, who had the honor, some
thirty years since, to attend on your highness in your infancy.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the curving pieces of wood or metal on which
a cradle, chair, etc., rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Any implement or machine working with a rocking
motion, as a trough mounted on rockers for separating gold dust from
gravel, etc., by agitation in water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A play horse on rockers; a rocking-horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A chair mounted on rockers; a
rocking-chair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A skate with a curved blade, somewhat resembling in
shape the rocker of a cradle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Rock
shaft</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rocker arm</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>an arm borne
by a rock shaft.</cd></cs> <-- <col><b>To be off one's rocker</b></col>,
<cd>to be insane.</cd> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rockered</ent>⟦br⟧
